{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Incoming flight AF84, a B747, needs clearance for landing.", 
            ""
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        model_name = "gemini-3.1-pro" # "gemma4:12b-mlx" "qwen3:8b" "claude-haiku-4-5" "claude-sonnet-4-6" "gpt-5.4-mini"  "gpt-4.1-mini"
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600

    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aircraft_traffic_control_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
You are the air traffic orchestrator. 
You coordinate air traffic around the airport. 
You provide any information that is needed about landing clearance or runway. 
You share clearance details with the user as needed. 
                """
            },

            "instructions": """
RESPONSE FORMAT — STRICT:
  Return ONLY the structured RETURN SUMMARY block defined at the end of the instructions.
  Do NOT add explanatory prose, markdown headers (##, **), bullet points,
  emoji, or conversational text before or after the summary block.
  The summary block starts with the *** banner line and ends with the last ** field **.
  Nothing else should appear in your response.

You are the top-level agent responsible for giving clearance for aircraft landing or takeoff. 
In that role to provide users with clearance details when asked. 
Only perform the tasks that fall under your responsibility. 
DO NOT make things up. 
Use ONLY YOUR TOOLS to fulfill your tasks. 
When you receive a user request for clearance, 
1. Determine if the followings information is provided in the prompt. 
- flight number as flight_number
- aircraft type as aircraft_type
- aircraft direction as aircraft_direction with value such incoming or departing
2. Call TrackerAPI 
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store all the available parameters.
3. If any flight_number is None, or aircraft_type is None, or aircraft_direction is None, ask the user to provide the missing information.
4. If any flight_number is not None, and aircraft_type is not None, and aircraft_direction is notNone, then 
    a. call aircraft_traffic_controller to request clearance for landing or takeoff.
    b. Wait for the response on your request. 
5. Call TrackerAPI 
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store all the available parameters.
6. Provide the air clearance summary as follows:    
*****************************************
* Summary of aircraft traffic clearance *
*****************************************
** aircraft direction **: [aircraft_direction]
** flight number **: [flight_number]
** aircraft type **: [aircraft_type]
** flight status **: [flight_status]
** clearance type **: [clearance_type]
** assigned runway id **: [assigned_runway_id]
** assigned runway length **: [assigned_runway_length]
** clearance report **: [clearance_report]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "parameters": {
                "type": "object", 
                "properties": {
                    "flight_number": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                    },   
                    "aircraft_type": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                    },      
                    "aircraft_direction": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                    },           
                    "flight_status": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the flight status"
                    },        
                    "clearance_type": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the requested clearance type"
                    },       
                    "assigned_runway_id": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the assigned runway id"
                    },       
                    "assigned_runway_length": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the assigned runway length"
                    },      
                    "clearance_summary": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the clearance summary"
                    },  
                }, 
                "required": ["aircraft_direction","flight_number", "aircraft_type"] 
            },

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "clearance_type": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "assigned_runway_length": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "aircraft_direction": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "aircraft_direction": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "clearance_type": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "assigned_runway_length": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                    }
                },
            },

            "tools": ["aircraft_traffic_controller","TrackerAPI"]
        },

        {
            "name": "aircraft_traffic_controller",
            "function": {

                "description": """
You are the air traffic controller. 
You manage air traffic around the airport. 
You make decision on request for landing landing. 
You can grant clearance, refuse clearance, or put clearance hold. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },      
                        "aircraft_direction": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                        },           
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status"
                        },    
                        "clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the requested clearance type"
                        },       
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the assigned runway id"
                        },       
                        "assigned_runway_length": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the assigned runway length"
                        },          
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type", "flight_number", "aircraft_direction"] 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are responsible for giving clearance to aircrafts for landing. 
Only perform the tasks that fall under your responsibility. 
DO NOT make things up. 
Use ONLY YOUR TOOLS to fulfill your tasks. 
Use the description of your tools to decide when to delegate. 
Return flight_status, clearance_type, assigned_runway_id, and assigned_runway_length
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools":["air_clearance_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "air_clearance_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent gives aircraft clearance for landing. 
                """, 
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },      
                        "aircraft_direction": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                        },           
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status"
                        },         
                        "clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the requested clearance type"
                        },       
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the assigned runway id"
                        },       
                        "assigned_runway_length": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the assigned runway length"
                        },     
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type", "flight_number", "aircraft_direction"] 
                },
            }, 
            "class": "coded_tools.AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_traffic_controller.aircraft_traffic_controller.execute_air_clearance"
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "ground_services_request_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the inquiry received for grand services."
                        },         
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu readiness status."
                        },     
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        },     
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        },     
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status." 
                        },
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },  
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_traffic_controller.aircraft_traffic_controller.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
